subSubSection.paragraph:
Neralsia haddocki can be separated from all other described world Neralsia species by the closed marginal cell. A defined true vein is present along the wing margin completely closing the marginal cell. A number of the Central American and West Indies species have a darkening on the wing margin, but this is not considered to be a true vein (
Jimenez et al. 2008b
). The carina present between the scutellar fovea is at the same height as the outer foveal edge.
